The world has turned upside down.

00:45:25.180 --> 00:45:27.999
It feels different. It's fun.

00:45:31.645 --> 00:45:34.239
I can only see your double chin.

00:45:47.745 --> 00:45:49.955
There's a contemporary artist in Germany.

00:45:49.955 --> 00:45:53.292
His name is Georg Baselitz.

00:45:53.292 --> 00:45:55.593
He painted upside down.

00:45:56.295 --> 00:46:00.466
At first, I didn't understand
why he painted like that.

00:46:00.466 --> 00:46:03.059
But later on, I think I got it.

00:46:04.136 --> 00:46:06.430
In his paintings,

00:46:06.430 --> 00:46:08.348
although it's chaotic,

00:46:08.348 --> 00:46:10.356
it has its own rules.

00:46:11.935 --> 00:46:14.622
That's his upside-down world.

00:46:16.815 --> 00:46:20.743
The sky that day
was as beautiful as it is today.

00:46:23.989 --> 00:46:26.026
The day my mom committed suicide.

00:46:32.456 --> 00:46:35.375
She couldn't stand
my dad's constant infidelity.

00:46:35.375 --> 00:46:36.377
Mom.

00:46:36.377 --> 00:46:38.504
She chose a beautiful afternoon

00:46:38.504 --> 00:46:40.555
and jumped off our rooftop.

00:46:44.009 --> 00:46:45.893
Right in front of me.

00:46:49.765 --> 00:46:52.006
She was saved,

00:46:53.393 --> 00:46:55.283
but became a vegetable.

00:47:27.970 --> 00:47:30.056
Perhaps it's the people who are upside down,

00:47:31.098 --> 00:47:33.020
not the world.

